description: Laugh with Europe's comedy nomad Victor Patrascan as he tells hilarious jokes while asking thought-provoking questions on today‚Äôs most controversial topics. You'll hear jokes on subjects like race and religion all the way to gender and politics. This show is not for the easily offended! Don‚Äôt miss out on Victor‚Äôs newest jokes! Victor‚Äôs set includes entirely new jokes not heard during his previous appearance in town. Perfect for locals expats and immigrants this show invites everyone to laugh at modern life‚Äôs absurdities. Join us for a show where comedy is at its best - insightful honest and uproariously funny. üé≠ STAND-UP COMEDY in ENGLISH üé≠ üéüÔ∏è online tickets from 500 MKD / tickets on the door 1000 MKD Tickets: https://fienta.com/stand-up-comedy-in-broken-english-victor-patrascan-skopje üö´ 16+ age limit The show will be held entirely in English. Victor Patrascan üá∑üá¥ ‚Ä¢ VictorPatrascan.com ‚Ä¢ @VictorPatrascan Victor P√£tr√£≈ücan is an eccentric stand up comedian and outrageous social commentator from Romania. He‚Äôs been on tour consistently for the last 5 years with his self-produced shows all over Europe and Asia. He is now on probably the longest and most extensive self-produced comedy show ever in the world. He honed his craft for joke writing in the London comedy circuit where he lived until 2020. Since then he has lived on the road and has been constantly on tour. In some places such as Kazakhstan Kosovo or in remote fishing villages in Iceland he was the first comedian to ever perform comedy in English. Victor has told his jokes in Japan Germany Italy the Netherlands Greece Austria Singapore Turkiye Sweden France Serbia Switzerland Georgia Finland Belgium Iceland Ukraine Albania Malta Serbia Spain Estonia Italy Cyprus (both sides) Ireland South Korea Liechtenstein Portugal Kosovo Gibraltar Kazakhstan the Czech Republic Iceland Norway Slovakia very close to the Vatican Thailand Georgia UK Slovenia Armenia Croatia Poland Latvia North Macedonia Lithuania Luxembourg UAE Denmark Moldova Vietnam Hungary and even Bulgaria. In 2024 alone Victor self-produced 298 shows and performed to over 35000 people on 2 continents in 48 countries and 114 cities. Victor‚Äôs style is distinctly shaped by his peculiar life as a vagabond. Victor weaves this unique experience into his stand up as he has become somewhat of a sponge absorbing the intricacies of European culture and politics. While he jokes about the stereotypes and misconceptions of every country he also highlights the silliness of our presumed differences in an effort to assert our humanity. –°–≤–µ—Ç—Å–∫–∞—Ç–∞ –¢—Ä–∏–∞—Ç–ª–æ–Ω –§–µ–¥–µ—Ä–∞—Ü–∏—ò–∞ –∑–∞ 2025 –≥–æ–¥–∏–Ω–∞. It is our great pleasure to invite you to the fifth Stopanska Triogy Triathlon in Skopje, our capital. This race is organized by Skopje's Triathlon Club Triogy Racing, with technical assistance from the Triathlon Federation of North Macedonia. The race will take place on September 28th, 2025 at the Boris Trajkovski Sports Center. The race will begin with a swim in the Boris Trajkovski Swimming Pool, followed by a bike ride along Ilinden Boulevard and a run around the Boris Trajkovski Sports Center. Categories: - Seniors (2005 and older): 750m swimming, 20km cycling, 5km running; - Juniors (2006-2009): 750m swimming, 20km cycling, 5km running; - Cadets (2010-2012): 375m swimming, 10km cycling, 2.5km running. - Children 2 (2013-2015): 175m swimming, 4km cycling, 1km running; - Children 1 (2016 and younger - recreational category): 75m swimming, 2km cycling, 500m running; - Masters 1 (1995-1986): 750m swimming, 20km cycling, 5km running; - Masters 2 (1985-1976): 750m swimming, 20km cycling, 5km running; - Masters 3 (1975 and older): 750m swim, 20km bike, 5km run; - Team triathlon: Teams should have three members (at least one male and one female participant). Each participant relays one of the sprint distance disciplines: 750m swimming, 20km cycling, or 5km running. The minimum age for the bicycle segment and the run is 16 years, and the minimum age for swimming is over 10 years with a parent's statement. Link to registartion: https://triologyracing.trki.mk/mk/events/stopanska-triogi-triatlon-2025 ‚ö†Ô∏èIMPORTANT FOR ALL COMPETITORS: TECHNICAL RULES FOR PARTICIPATION Participants are obliged to respect the rules of ITU and TFSM. Participation in the race is at one's own responsibility and all consequences are the responsibility of the competitors. description: Get ready to explore the untouched beauty of National Park Galichica from September 5 - 7, 2025. Nestled between the stunning Lake Ohrid and Lake Prespa, this adventure is your ticket to three unforgettable days in nature's paradise. HIGHLANDER Pegasus (September 5 - 7, 2025): A three-day, fully immersive hiking journey for adventurers seeking to push their limits while soaking in the region's stunning beauty. HIGHLANDER Orion (September 6 - 7, 2025): A condensed, two-day hike perfect for those looking to experience the magic of Galichica at a slightly shorter pace. Both formats offer hikers a chance to traverse the park‚Äôs diverse terrains, which include rugged mountain peaks, serene valleys, and expansive meadows. Participants will be surrounded by panoramic views of the lakes and the unique flora and fauna that make this area a biodiversity hotspot.
